// Project: Variables Xporter
// Type: Figma Plugin with Documentation
// Purpose: Export Figma variables to Tailwind CSS and CSS variables

// Workspace Structure
1. Figma Plugin (/figma-plugin):
   - Framework: React + TypeScript
   - Build Tool: Vite
   - UI Framework: Mantine
   - State Management: React Context
   - Key Files:
     - src/lib/utils2.ts (Core variable processing logic)
     - src/app/components/App.tsx (Main plugin UI)
     - src/lib/type.ts (TypeScript type definitions)

2. Documentation Site (/docs):
   - Framework: Next.js
   - Content: MDX
   - UI Framework: Nextra
   - Language: Chinese (中文)
   - Key Directories:
     - app/docs/ (Documentation content)
     - public/ (Static assets)

// Core Features
1. Export Modes:
   - Tailwind CSS configuration export
   - CSS variables export

2. Multi-mode System:
   - Supports dark/light modes
   - Brand themes
   - Responsive breakpoints
   - Special states
   - And more...
   - Single outlet principle for variable references

3. Variable Organization:
   - Uses "/" for grouping (e.g. colors/primary)
   - Supports DEFAULT keyword for base values
   - Follows Tailwind CSS theme structure
   - Semantic naming conventions

// Key Principles
1. Variable Organization:
   - Clear naming conventions
   - Logical grouping
   - Tailwind CSS compatibility
   - Maintainability

2. Multi-mode Support:
   - Single outlet principle
   - Clear reference chains
   - Mode inheritance
   - Flexible configuration

3. Export Rules:
   - Maintains variable relationships
   - Preserves mode structure
   - Supports customization
   - Handles unit conversion

// Documentation Structure
1. Getting Started
2. Multi-mode System
3. Export Modes
4. Variable Organization
5. Advanced Features
6. Troubleshooting
